Python

=======

This folder should contain helper scripts, or anything that could be relevant for Python.

Think about specific plots manipulations, or data loading/handling.

These programs output a plot in /tmp/plot.pdf by default.

=======

Content:

qq -- produce a Quantile-Quantile plot of the first and second column of input.
histo -- produce a histogram of the first column of input
pl -- general line plots. see comments at start of file for usage.

transpose -- swap rows and columns (note: loads entire file into memory)
rmstop -- remove stop works from a stream of text
ngrams -- produce all n-grams of text, one per line.

